primaryTopic.definition: The University was originally founded in Rockhampton in 1967 and was known as the Queensland Institute of Technology (Capricornia), achieving full university status in 1992. Its main campus is in North Rockhampton, Queensland. Along with locations in regional Queensland (Bundaberg, Emerald, Gladstone, and Mackay), CQUniversity has also expanded its presence throughout Australia with campuses in Adelaide, Brisbane, Melbourne, Noosa and Sydney, Study Centres in Biloela and Yeppoon, a Cairns Distance Education Study Centre, a delivery site in Edithvale, Victoria, and Partner Study Hubs in Cannonvale, Queensland and Geraldton, Western Australia.
